column5: Does anyone know any details about the tornado south of Minden?
no, just south of Minden, from Hunter Creek to the south end of Bob Lake
My dad lost 4 tree's and has no power on 4 mile lake right now.

Local news said they expect hydro crews in the area to restore power within 4 to 5 days  they showed a few shots of the bridge area..a lot of damage.  I suspect that the Minden through Irondale area got about the same.
I don't think he lost them  he knows where they are   they are now just vertically challenged.......    :rofl2:  sorry  I do hope they didn't hit anything
true.  the 1 fell and blocked the road and the others fell in the yard.  the 1 was cleaned up ASAP so they could get in and the others are going to be cleand up tomorrow.
From what I saw on the news... none of those trees came down from a tornado.

we got hit hard on sturgeon lake in dunsford,the nieghbors 17ft bayliner with a 90hp is upside down in the lake,lots of docks ruined trees down too,we might have power by late tonight....dam this is the second time this year alone !!!!! grrrrrr

Yup, saw on news yesterday that the wind damage in the area is from a microburst not tornadoes after Enviroment Canada sent teams to survey damage. Still sounds like lots of trees down right through the Kawarthas etc...

I got to see it from the water. Let me tell ya, I've never seen a storm appear that quick. She was dirty. I was lucky to make it to shore in time. I wish I could have taken pictures of the boat ride to shore. Just crazy!!  S.
A valuable learning expierance. Happy to hear every thing is ok.  I hit 8 to 10 ft with rouge waves a few years ago. Scared the hell out of me. Kilarny.
